<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8276&amp;p=85946#p85946"><![CDATA[
Try applying some compression (as in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamic_range_compression" class="postlink">dynamic range compression</a>, not data compression) to the speech to even out the volume levels. Overall the speech part has much lower volume than the intro tune. Also the intro tune is too long, IMO.<br /><br />Good luck with the podcast.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Sun Nov 06, 2011 9:40 pm</p><hr />
