I'm listening to it right now! <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br /><br />Right off the bat I notice you have the same problem I do: trying to read &amp; sound natural. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> <br /><br />You could adlib, but if you're like me (not a good talker) then this is <em>probably</em> not a good option.<br /><br />Actors have this same problem (&amp; they're not even reading!). You just need to keep practicing; it will eventually come.<br /><br />As for the sound mixing, I think it's okay. Some people might think the music needs to brought up more, but it's really up to you. I think it works as it is right now - it's not distracting.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=984">Jedi QuestMaster</a> — Sun Nov 06, 2011 9:26 pm</p><hr />
