<title type="html"><![CDATA[Started my own retro gaming podcast. Thoughts?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8276&amp;p=85896#p85896"><![CDATA[
Hey guys, you may know me from my youtube channel or my blog that I'm a big retro gamer. As I continue to write the top 100 NES games of all time on my blog, I got an email from a subscriber who suggested I start my own podcast. Thinking it over, I consulted my gamer friends for their inputs and asked around in various forums for some advice and well, I've decided to give it a go.<br /><br />I've produced this prototype episode of what may be a podcast. Before I create an itunes or rrs feed, I just want to see what people think and if I should actually bother to do this kind of thing. I'm thinking I'd do a bi-weekly (possibly weekly) podcast to begin with and see what people think.<br /><br />So with some feedback I've received I've tried to make this as good as possible, but keep in mind I'm new at this and find balancing volume levels difficult, but I did try my best. For now, please let me know your thoughts.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.megaupload.com/?d=FDOTYXHH">http://www.megaupload.com/?d=FDOTYXHH</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4236">SatoshiMatrix</a> — Sat Nov 05, 2011 1:44 pm</p><hr />
